Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Cut @zucchini{1} into ½-inch cubes. Combine @chicken breasts{12%ounce}, @berbere{1%teaspoon}, half the @yogurt{1} and a large pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{} in a #medium bowl{}. Turn to thoroughly coat in marinade.

> Berbere is an Ethiopian spice blend with garlic, red pepper, cardamom, coriander, and fenugreek.

== Rice Pilaf ==

Make the rice pilaf: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onions and garlic, and toss until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @basmati rice{3/4%cup} and stir. Add 1 1/2 cups water, a large pinch of salt, and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, cover, then reduce to a low simmer until tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

== Chicken and Zucchini ==

Place chicken on one half of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Broil until slightly charred, ~{3-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, toss zucchini in a medium bowl with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Remove baking sheet from oven, flip chicken, and reduce heat to 425 degrees. Spread zucchini on other half of baking sheet. Bake until chicken is no longer pink inside and zucchini is tender, about ~{12%minutes}.

== Lemony Yogurt ==

Meanwhile, zest and halve @lemon{1}. Stir zest and a squeeze of juice into a #small bowl{} with remaining yogurt. Thin with a Tablespoon or so of water. Season with salt and pepper.

== Finish and Serve ==

Finish the pilaf and serve: Coarsely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}, and stir half into rice pilaf. Serve zucchini and chicken on a bed of rice pilaf. Top with a dollop of lemony yogurt and a sprinkle of the remaining cilantro. Enjoy!